@node Main "Toptile - Documentation"

                              'Toptile' 1.0

                           by Charles-N. Jacob

  'Toptile' is a @{"Workbench game" link play} where the goal is to move all the
shapes that appear on hexagonal tiles, so they are placed at the
top of a triangular game board. When a shape is placed at the top
of the board, it is replaced by a 'neutral' shape. You get 1 point
or more according to the number of consecutive shapes of the same
type that have been placed at the top...

  To complicate matters a little, only a small portion of the game
board is displayed at all time. So you have to move on the game
board in order to fetch the needed shapes and move them to the top.
Additionnally, the shapes must be moved by following the links that
are placed between the hexagonal tiles.

  Have fun!

