@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "Toptile" where you want
on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files or
Libraries are needed. The only requirement is that your Workbench
must have at least 8 colours.

NOTE: I am not sure of this game's 'behaviour' on a stock 68000
      Amiga. For now, until somebody confirms that Toptile runs fine
      on a 68000 machine, this game will require an Amiga with a
      68020 or faster processor... sorry!

                             How to play?

  To move a shape, click on a link that connects two hexagonal
tiles together, then, the shapes that are located on them will
exchange their positions. If a shape, except a neutral shape, moves
to the top of the board, it will disappear and it will be replaced
by a neutral shape (a small 'embossed' rectangle), and you will get
1 point. If the previous shape that was put to the top was of the
same type, you will get additional points according to the number
of consecutive shapes of the same type, as shown below:

First shape:   1 point
Second shape:  3 points [1+2 points]
Third shape:   6 points [1+2+3 points]
Fourth shape: 10 points [1+2+3+4 points]
etc.

  To move on the game board, click on an hexagonal tile, except the
one located at the center. The game display will then be updated
and the tile you clicked on will be located at the center. Note
that you can also use the numbered keys of the numeric keypad to
move on the game board, the numbered keys are indicated below:

         7            9
    upper left   upper right

       4                6
     left             right

         1            3
    lower left   lower right

  When you complete a game board, Toptile will display a new game
board to play with. Try to complete each game board with the least
amount of moves...

  Have fun!

  You can quit the game by clicking on the main window's close
button or by pressing on the 'Esc' key.

